HEADWORD: Ganesha
<hw>Ganesha</hw></mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Hindu Myth.)</fld> <def>The
Hindu god of wisdom, prudence and prophesy; the remover of
obstacles.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Ganapati.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ He is represented as a short, fat, red-colored man, with
a large belly and the head of an elephant.</note>
<rj><au>Balfour.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gang</ent>⟦br⟧
